            "id": "1732617aeca641d8896aa",
            "questionText": "Calculate the fission Q-value, in $!$MeV$!$, for the spontaneous fission of Californium-252 ($!$^{252}Cf$!$) nucleus into Xenon-132 ($!$^{132}Xe$!$), Cerium-116 ($!$^{116}Ce$!$), and four neutrons ($!$4n$!$), given that $!$m(^{252}Cf)=252.081626\\,u$!$, $!$m(^{132}Xe)=131.904153\\,u$!$, $!$m(^{116}Ce)=115.903326\\,u$!$, $!$m(n)=1.008665\\,u$!$, and $!$1\\,u=931.5\\,\\frac{MeV}{c^2}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "5e685e6c3d9d478ea1966",
